Jeanette Chabalala, News24Jail. (File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Kimberley - A Northern Cape father was sentenced to life in prison for raping his daughter over a period of three years, police said on Thursday. The Calvinia Regional Court last week sentenced him to life, plus 26 years, for rape and sexual assault, Lieutenant-Colonel Dimakatso Mooi said.&nbsp;The sentences would run concurrently.&nbsp;Mooi said the 52-year-old man had been molesting his daughter since 2000, when she was 9. He made her believe he was preparing her to be a young lady, she said. &nbsp;The daughter reported what&nbsp;her father was doing in July 2013.&nbsp;&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.